gwInfoModel.name: gwInfoModel
gwInfoModel.description: This object indicates the Gateway Model Number.

gwInfoSerialNumber.name: gwInfoSerialNumber
gwInfoSerialNumber.description: This object indicates the Gateway Serial Number.

gwInfoLanMac.name: gwInfoLanMac
gwInfoLanMac.description: This object indicates the Gateway's LAN port MAC Address.

gwInfoWanMac.name: gwInfoWanMac
gwInfoWanMac.description: This object indicates the Gateway's WAN port MAC Address.

gwInfoPlcMac.name: gwInfoPlcMac
gwInfoPlcMac.description: This object indicates the Gateway PLC MAC Address

gwInfoHardwareVer.name: gwInfoHardwareVer
gwInfoHardwareVer.description: This object indicates the Gateway Hardware Version.

gwInfoDevFirmwareVer.name: gwInfoDevFirmwareVer
gwInfoDevFirmwareVer.description: This object indicates the Gateway Device Firmware Version.

gwInfoLoaderVer.name: gwInfoLoaderVer
gwInfoLoaderVer.description: This object indicates the Gateway Loader Version.

gwInfoSimFirmwareVer.name: gwInfoSimFirmwareVer
gwInfoSimFirmwareVer.description: This object indicates the Intellon Simple Module Firmware Version.

gwInfoModemCount.name: gwInfoModemCount
gwInfoModemCount.description: This object indicates the number of Modems registered to the Gateway.

gwInfoDeviceUpgradeStatus.name: gwInfoDeviceUpgradeStatus
gwInfoDeviceUpgradeStatus.description: This object indicates the Gateway Last Software Upgrade Status. 0 - Upgrade not started 1 - Upgrade in progress 2 - Last Upgrade failed 3 - Last Upgrade was successful.

gwInfoSimUpgradeStatus.name: gwInfoSimUpgradeStatus
gwInfoSimUpgradeStatus.description: This object indicates the Intellon Simple Module's last Software Upgrade Status. 0 - Upgrade not started 1 - Upgrade in progress 2 - Last Upgrade failed 3 - Last Upgrade was successful.

gwInfoTemperature.name: gwInfoTemperature
gwInfoTemperature.description: This object indicates the ambient temperature of the Gateway.

gwConfNtpConfig.name: gwConfNtpConfig
gwConfNtpConfig.description: This object is used to Enable or Disable the Gateway to set it's system clock using NTP.

gwConfNtpServer.name: gwConfNtpServer
gwConfNtpServer.description: This object is used to configure the NTP Server.

gwConfTime.name: gwConfTime
gwConfTime.description: This object is used to configure Gateway's system clock time. The input format is HH:MM::SS. This object is accessible only if gwConfNtpConfig is disabled.

gwConfDate.name: gwConfDate
gwConfDate.description: This object is used to configure Gateway's system clock date. The input format is YYYY/MM/DD. This object is accessible only if gwConfNtpConfig is disabled.

gwConfModemTableTimeout.name: gwConfModemTableTimeout
gwConfModemTableTimeout.description: This object is used to configure the Modem Table Timeout. Any Inactive Modem will be deleted from the Modem table, if it is inactive for a period more than the timeout value.

gwConfAutoLogoutTime.name: gwConfAutoLogoutTime
gwConfAutoLogoutTime.description: This object is used to configure the Gateway Auto Logout Time. User will be logged out of the Gateway's web interface, if there is inactivity for a period more than the Auto Logout Time.

gwConfPSD.name: gwConfPSD
gwConfPSD.description: This object indicates the Power Spectral Density of the signal, at all the 84 carriers, that the device transmits. Starting at the left most octet, which represents the spectral value at channel number 0, each octet represents the spectral value at the corresponding channel number. The channel numbers 4, 5, 13, 14, 29, 49, 50, 51, 69 and 70 are masked and their spectral values cannot be changed.

gwConfTrapIp1.name: gwConfTrapIp1
gwConfTrapIp1.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #1.

gwConfTrapCommStr1.name: gwConfTrapCommStr1
gwConfTrapCommStr1.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #1.

gwConfTrapIp2.name: gwConfTrapIp2
gwConfTrapIp2.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #2.

gwConfTrapCommStr2.name: gwConfTrapCommStr2
gwConfTrapCommStr2.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #2.

gwConfTrapIp3.name: gwConfTrapIp3
gwConfTrapIp3.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #3.

gwConfTrapCommStr3.name: gwConfTrapCommStr3
gwConfTrapCommStr3.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #3.

gwConfTrapIp4.name: gwConfTrapIp4
gwConfTrapIp4.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #4.

gwConfTrapCommStr4.name: gwConfTrapCommStr4
gwConfTrapCommStr4.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #4.

gwConfTrapIp5.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #5.

gwConfTrapCommStr5.name: gwConfTrapCommStr5
gwConfTrapCommStr5.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #5.

gwConfTrapIp6.name: gwConfTrapIp6
gwConfTrapIp6.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #6.

gwConfTrapCommStr6.name: gwConfTrapCommStr6
gwConfTrapCommStr6.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #6.

gwConfTrapIp7.name: gwConfTrapIp7
gwConfTrapIp7.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #7.

gwConfTrapCommStr7.name: gwConfTrapCommStr7
gwConfTrapCommStr7.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #7.

gwConfTrapIp8.name: gwConfTrapIp8
gwConfTrapIp8.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #8.

gwConfTrapCommStr8.name: gwConfTrapCommStr8
gwConfTrapCommStr8.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #8.

gwConfTrapIp9.name: gwConfTrapIp9
gwConfTrapIp9.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #9.

gwConfTrapCommStr9.name: gwConfTrapCommStr9
gwConfTrapCommStr9.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #9.

gwConfTrapIp10.name: gwConfTrapIp10
gwConfTrapIp10.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of SNMP Trap Client #10.

gwConfTrapCommStr10.name: gwConfTrapCommStr10
gwConfTrapCommStr10.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Community string for Trap Client #10.

gwPwrLnMaxDelay.name: gwPwrLnMaxDelay
gwPwrLnMaxDelay.description: This object indicates the Maximum transfer delay on Powerline.

gwPwrLnTxAck.name: gwPwrLnTxAck
gwPwrLnTxAck.description: This object indicates the Powerline Transmit ACK count.

gwPwrLnTxNak.name: gwPwrLnTxNak
gwPwrLnTxNak.description: This object indicates the Powerline Transmit NACK count.

gwPwrLnTxFail.name: gwPwrLnTxFail
gwPwrLnTxFail.description: This object indicates the Powerline Transmission Failures.

gwPwrLnTxColl.name: gwPwrLnTxColl
gwPwrLnTxColl.description: This object indicates the Powerline Transmission Collisions.

gwPwrLnTxCarrLoss.name: gwPwrLnTxCarrLoss
gwPwrLnTxCarrLoss.description: This object indicates the Powerline Transmt Carrier Loss Detection.

gwPwrLnRoboByte40.name: gwPwrLnRoboByte40
gwPwrLnRoboByte40.description: This object indicates the raw value of channel capacity as reported by Intellon PHY

gwPwrLnRoboFails.name: gwPwrLnRoboFails
gwPwrLnRoboFails.description: This object indicates the Powerline protocol receive failures, in ROBO mode.

gwPwrLnRoboDrops.name: gwPwrLnRoboDrops
gwPwrLnRoboDrops.description: This object indicates the Powerline protocol transmit drops, in ROBO mode.

gwAdmConfLoginUsername.name: gwAdmConfLoginUsername
gwAdmConfLoginUsername.description: This object is used to configure Gateway's System Management Login Username.

gwAdmConfLoginPassword.name: gwAdmConfLoginPassword
gwAdmConfLoginPassword.description: This object is used to configure Gateway's System Management Login Password.

gwAdmConfNEK.name: gwAdmConfNEK
gwAdmConfNEK.description: This object is used to configure Network Encryption Key of the Gateway.

gwAdmConfAuthServIp1.name: gwAdmConfAuthServIp1
gwAdmConfAuthServIp1.description: This object is used to configure BAM Server #1 IP Address.

gwAdmConfAuthServIp2.name: gwAdmConfAuthServIp2
gwAdmConfAuthServIp2.description: This object is used to configure BAM Server #2 IP Address.

gwAdmConfAuthServIp3.name: gwAdmConfAuthServIp3
gwAdmConfAuthServIp3.description: This object is used to configure BAM Server #3 IP Address.

gwAdmConfAuthMode.name: gwAdmConfAuthMode
gwAdmConfAuthMode.description: This object is used to Enable or Disable BAM Authentication on the Gateway.

gwAdmConfAuthKey.name: gwAdmConfAuthKey
gwAdmConfAuthKey.description: This object is used to configure Authentication Key, to use with BAM Server, on the Gateway.

gwAdmConfAuthKeyOption.name: gwAdmConfAuthKeyOption
gwAdmConfAuthKeyOption.description: This object is used to configure the Authentication Key to be used, on the Gateway.

gwAdmConfSnmpGetCommStr.name: gwAdmConfSnmpGetCommStr
gwAdmConfSnmpGetCommStr.description: This object is used to configure SNMP 'Read' community string of the Gateway.

gwAdmConfSnmpSetCommStr.name: gwAdmConfSnmpSetCommStr
gwAdmConfSnmpSetCommStr.description: This object is used to configure SNMP 'Read-Write' community string of the Gateway.

gwAdmConfSnmpAdminCommStr.name: gwAdmConfSnmpAdminCommStr
gwAdmConfSnmpAdminCommStr.description: This object is used to configure SNMP 'Admin' community string of the Gateway.

gwAdmConfFtpServerIp.name: gwAdmConfFtpServerIp
gwAdmConfFtpServerIp.description: This object is used to configure IP Address of FTP server hosting auto-upgrade files.

gwAdmConfFtpUsername.name: gwAdmConfFtpUsername
gwAdmConfFtpUsername.description: This object is used to configure Username to login to a FTP server, for use with FTP-based auto-upgrade.

gwAdmConfFtpPassword.name: gwAdmConfFtpPassword
gwAdmConfFtpPassword.description: This object is used to configure Password to login to a FTP server, for use with FTP-based auto-upgrade.

gwAdmConfFtpFile.name: gwAdmConfFtpFile
gwAdmConfFtpFile.description: This object is used to configure Path and/or Filename of the firmware file, for use with FTP-based auto-upgrade.

gwAdmConfDeviceUpgradeStart.name: gwAdmConfDeviceUpgradeStart
gwAdmConfDeviceUpgradeStart.description: This object is used to Start Device Firmware Upgrade process in the Gateway. To start the upgrade process, this object should be set to '1'.

gwAdmConfSimUpgradeStart.name: gwAdmConfSimUpgradeStart
gwAdmConfSimUpgradeStart.description: This object is used to start Intellon Simple Module Firmware Upgrade process in the Gateway. To start the upgrade process, this object should be set to '1'.

gwAdmConfSystemReboot.name: gwAdmConfSystemReboot
gwAdmConfSystemReboot.description: This object is used to Reboot the Gateway. To reboot the Gateway, this object should be set to '1'.

gwAdmConfReset.name: gwAdmConfReset
gwAdmConfReset.description: This object is used to reset the Gateway configuration to Factory Defaults. To reset the Gateway configuration to factory defaults, this object should be set to '1'.

gwAdmConfDeviceMode.name: gwAdmConfDeviceMode
gwAdmConfDeviceMode.description: This object is used to configure the device in 'switch' mode or 'NAT' mode.

gwAdmConfLUIDStart.name: gwAdmConfLUIDStart
gwAdmConfLUIDStart.description: This object is used to configure the starting value of the Modem LUID range. This value should not be greater than gwAdmConfLUIDEnd value

gwAdmConfLUIDEnd.name: gwAdmConfLUIDEnd
gwAdmConfLUIDEnd.description: This object is used to configure the ending value of the Modem LUID range. This value should not be less than gwAdmConfLUIDStart value

gwAdmConfVLANPassthroughStatus.name: gwAdmConfVLANPassthroughStatus
gwAdmConfVLANPassthroughStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable VLAN Passthrough feature.

gwAdmConfManagementVLANId.name: gwAdmConfManagementVLANId
gwAdmConfManagementVLANId.description: This object is used to enable or disable VLAN Passthrough feature.

gwAdmConfLanConfig.name: gwAdmConfLanConfig
gwAdmConfLanConfig.description: This object is used to Enable or Disable DHCP client.

gwAdmConfLanIp.name: gwAdmConfLanIp
gwAdmConfLanIp.description: This object is used to configure LAN IP Address.

gwAdmConfLanSubnetMask.name: gwAdmConfLanSubnetMask
gwAdmConfLanSubnetMask.description: This object is used to configure LAN IP Subnet Mask.

gwAdmConfLanGatewayIp.name: gwAdmConfLanGatewayIp
gwAdmConfLanGatewayIp.description: This object is used to configure Gateway IP Address.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork1.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork1
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork1.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #1.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask1.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask1
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask1.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #1.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork2.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork2
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork2.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #2.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask2.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask2
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask2.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #2.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork3.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork3
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork3.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #3.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask3.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask3
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask3.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #3.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork4.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork4
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork4.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #4.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask4.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask4
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask4.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #4.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork5.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork5
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork5.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #5.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask5.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask5
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask5.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #5.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork6.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork6
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork6.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #6.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask6.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask6
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask6.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #6.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork7.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork7
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork7.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #7.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask7.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask7
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask7.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #7.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork8.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork8
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork8.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #8.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask8.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask8
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask8.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #8.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork9.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork9
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork9.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #9.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask9.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask9
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask9.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #9.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork10.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork10
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetwork10.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address #10.

gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask10.name: gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask10
gwAdmSnmpAccessIpNetworkMask10.description: This object is used to configure SNMP Access Network Address Mask #10.

gwAdmWConfWanConfig.name: gwAdmWConfWanConfig
gwAdmWConfWanConfig.description: This object is used to configure the WAN Type. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfWanIp.name: gwAdmWConfWanIp
gwAdmWConfWanIp.description: This object is used to configure WAN IP Address of the Gateway. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfSubnetMask.name: gwAdmWConfSubnetMask
gwAdmWConfSubnetMask.description: This object is used to configure WAN IP Subnet Mask of the Gateway. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfGateway.name: gwAdmWConfGateway
gwAdmWConfGateway.description: This object is used to configure Default Gateway IP of the Gateway. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfDNS1.name: gwAdmWConfDNS1
gwAdmWConfDNS1.description: This object is used to configure DNS Server #1. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfDNS2.name: gwAdmWConfDNS2
gwAdmWConfDNS2.description: This object is used to configure DNS Server #2. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfPppoeUsername.name: gwAdmWConfPppoeUsername
gwAdmWConfPppoeUsername.description: This object is used to configure PPPoE Username. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfPppoePassword.name: gwAdmWConfPppoePassword
gwAdmWConfPppoePassword.description: This object is used to configure PPPoE Password. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfDhcpConfig.name: gwAdmWConfDhcpConfig
gwAdmWConfDhcpConfig.description: This object is used to Enable or Disable DHCP Server. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfDhcpStartIp.name: gwAdmWConfDhcpStartIp
gwAdmWConfDhcpStartIp.description: This object is used to configure Starting Address of the IP address block, that the DHCP Server can assign to its clients. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfDhcpEndIp.name: gwAdmWConfDhcpEndIp
gwAdmWConfDhcpEndIp.description: This object is used to configure Last Address of the IP address block, that the DHCP Server can assign to its clients. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfDhcpLeaseTime.name: gwAdmWConfDhcpLeaseTime
gwAdmWConfDhcpLeaseTime.description: This object is used to configure time period for which the IP address assigned to a client is valid. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfUpnpConfig.name: gwAdmWConfUpnpConfig
gwAdmWConfUpnpConfig.description: This object is used to Enable or Disable the UPnP in the Gateway. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

gwAdmWConfFirewallConfig.name: gwAdmWConfFirewallConfig
gwAdmWConfFirewallConfig.description: This object is used to Enable or Disable Firewall in the Gateway. This object is accessible only if the Gateway is in NAT mode.

whispPlvGwModemTable.name: whispPlvGwModemTable
whispPlvGwModemTable.description: This table contains one row per Modem registered to the Gateway.

whispPlvGwModemEntry.name: whispPlvGwModemEntry
whispPlvGwModemEntry.description: Information about a particular Modem registered to the Gateway.

gwModemLUID.name: gwModemLUID
gwModemLUID.description: This object indicates the unique value assigned by the Gateway, to each Modem.

gwModemDescr.name: gwModemDescr
gwModemDescr.description: The value of this object should be same as the object 'sysName' of the Device registered to the Gateway.

gwModemPhysAddress.name: gwModemPhysAddress
gwModemPhysAddress.description: This object indicates the PLC MAC Address of the Modem.

gwModemIP.name: gwModemIP
gwModemIP.description: This object indicates the IP Address of the Modem.

gwModemHardwareVersion.name: gwModemHardwareVersion
gwModemHardwareVersion.description: This object indicates the Hardware Version of the Modem.

gwModemSoftwareVersion.name: gwModemSoftwareVersion
gwModemSoftwareVersion.description: This object indicates the Software Version of the Modem.

gwModemSoftwareBootVersion.name: gwModemSoftwareBootVersion
gwModemSoftwareBootVersion.description: This object indicates the Boot Loader Version of the Modem.

gwModemSessState.name: gwModemSessState
gwModemSessState.description: This object indicates the current Operational state of the Modem. 0 = Idle 1 = In Session 2 = Clearing 3 = Re-registration downlink reset 4 = Authentication Challenge 5 = Registering 6 = Not in use.

gwModemsessionCount.name: gwModemsessionCount
gwModemsessionCount.description: This object indicates the number of times the Modem is In and Out of session.

gwModemMtu.name: gwModemMtu
gwModemMtu.description: This object indicates the size of the largest datagram that can be sent and received by the Modem, in octets.

gwModemSpeed.name: gwModemSpeed
gwModemSpeed.description: This object indicates an estimate of Modem's current bandwidth, in Mbps.

gwModemInOctets.name: gwModemInOctets
gwModemInOctets.description: This object indicates the octets received by the Modem over Powerline, including framing characters. to each Modem.

gwModemInUcastPkts.name: gwModemInUcastPkts
gwModemInUcastPkts.description: This object indicates the number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

gwModemInNUcastPkts.name: gwModemInNUcastPkts
gwModemInNUcastPkts.description: This object indicates the number of subnetwork-broadcast and subnetwork-multiicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

gwModemInDiscards.name: gwModemInDiscards
gwModemInDiscards.description: This object indicates the number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

gwModemInError.name: gwModemInError
gwModemInError.description: This object indicates the number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

gwModemInUnknownProtos.name: gwModemInUnknownProtos
gwModemInUnknownProtos.description: This object indicates the number of packets received, but were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

gwModemOutOctets.name: gwModemOutOctets
gwModemOutOctets.description: This object indicates the total number of octets transmitted, including the framing characters.

gwModemOutUcastPkts.name: gwModemOutUcastPkts
gwModemOutUcastPkts.description: This object indicates the total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

gwModemOutNUcastPkts.name: gwModemOutNUcastPkts
gwModemOutNUcastPkts.description: This object indicates the total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non-unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

gwModemOutDiscards.name: gwModemOutDiscards
gwModemOutDiscards.description: This object indicates the number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

gwModemOutError.name: gwModemOutError
gwModemOutError.description: This object indicates the number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

gwModemOutQLen.name: gwModemOutQLen
gwModemOutQLen.description: This object indicates the number of packets in output packet queue.

gwModemRoboByte40.name: gwModemRoboByte40
gwModemRoboByte40.description: This object indicates the current channel receive capacity of the Modem.

gwModemRoboFails.name: gwModemRoboFails
gwModemRoboFails.description: This object indicates the Powerline link receive failures of the Modem.

gwModemRoboDrops.name: gwModemRoboDrops
gwModemRoboDrops.description: This object indicates the Powerline link send failures of the Modem.

gwModemDeviceType.name: gwModemDeviceType
gwModemDeviceType.description: This object indicates the Type of the Device registered to the Gateway 0 = Modem 1 = Repeater 2 = Other

gwModemPSD.name: gwModemPSD
gwModemPSD.description: This object indicates the Software Version of the Modem.

gwTrapRegComplete.name: gwTrapRegComplete
gwTrapRegComplete.description: This Notification is generated if the Modem has successfully registered to the Gateway.

gwTrapRegLost.name: gwTrapRegLost
gwTrapRegLost.description: This Notification is generated if the Modem entry is removed from the Gateway's Modem Table, after being inactive for a period more than 'gwConfModemTableTimeout' value.

gwTrapDeviceUpgradeStarted.name: gwTrapDeviceUpgradeStarted
gwTrapDeviceUpgradeStarted.description: This Notification is generated if the Gateway has started the Device Firmware Upgrade process.

gwTrapDeviceUpgradeCompleted.name: gwTrapDeviceUpgradeCompleted
gwTrapDeviceUpgradeCompleted.description: This Notification is generated once the Device Firmware Upgrade process is completed.

gwTrapSimUpgradeStarted.name: gwTrapSimUpgradeStarted
gwTrapSimUpgradeStarted.description: This Notification is generated if the Gateway has started the Simple Module Firmware Upgrade process.

gwTrapSimUpgradeCompleted.name: gwTrapSimUpgradeCompleted
gwTrapSimUpgradeCompleted.description: This Notification is generated once the Simple Module Firmware Upgrade process is completed.

whispPlvGatewayInfoGroup.name: whispPlvGatewayInfoGroup
whispPlvGatewayInfoGroup.description: The collection of objects that indicates Gateway device information.

whispPlvGatewayConfigGroup.name: whispPlvGatewayConfigGroup
